<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Confirm Your WebAuthn Registration</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            background: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
        }
        p {
            color: #555;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .btn {
            display: block;
            width: 100%%;
            max-width: 250px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 12px;
            background: #007bff;
            color: #ffffff;
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 16px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .btn:hover {
            background: #0056b3;
        }
        .footer {
            font-size: 12px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #888;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Confirm Your WebAuthn Registration</h1>
        <p>You're just <strong>one click away</strong> from joining the password-free revolution! No more weak passwords like <code>password123</code>; WebAuthn is here to save the day.</p>
        <p>Click the button below to confirm your registration. But be warned: this is a <strong>one-time-use, self-destructing</strong> link! If you try clicking it again, you'll be greeted by a cold, lonely 404 page. 💥</p>
        <a href="%s" class="btn">Confirm Registration</a>
        <div class="footer">
            <p>Your copyright notice. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
